-- Japan, China, Malaysia, South Korea: Asian Local Bonds, Currency Preview
-- B y   A n d r e a   W o n g
-- 2010-10-13T21:14:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-13/japanese-yen-korean-won-malaysian-ringgit-asia-bonds-currency-preview.html
The following events and economic
reports may influence trading in Asia’s local bonds and
currencies today. Yields and exchange rates are from the
previous trading session unless stated otherwise.  Japan: Chief Cabinet Secretary  Yoshito Sengoku  will hold
media briefings at 11 a.m. and 4 p.m. in Tokyo.  The Bank of Japan will release at 8:50 a.m. in Tokyo its
report on the corporate goods price index for September. The
index was unchanged in September from a year earlier, according
to a Bloomberg News survey of economists.  The Ministry of Finance will announce at 10:30 a.m. in
Tokyo the amount of 20-year Japanese government bonds it plans
to sell on Oct. 21.  The yield on the 0.8 percent government bond due September
2020 was at 0.895 percent, according to Japan Bond Trading Co.,
the nation’s largest interdealer debt broker.  The yen traded at 81.79 per dollar at 6:08 a.m. in Tokyo.  China: The China Development Bank will sell 20 billion
yuan ($3 billion) of one-year bills today. The People’s Bank of
China will sell 31 billion yuan of 91-day debt and 16 billion
yuan of three-year notes.  The yield on the 2.53 percent note due June 2015 was 2.73
percent. The yuan was at 6.6641.  South Korea: The Bank of Korea Monetary Policy Committee
will keep the benchmark seven-day repurchase rate at 2.25
percent when it meets at 8 a.m. today in Seoul, according to a
Bloomberg News survey of economists.  The yield on the 3.75 percent debt due June 2013 was 3.28
percent, according to Korea Stock Exchange. The won traded at
1,115.90.  Malaysia: The central bank will sell 3.7 billion ringgit
($1.2 billion) of debt, comprising 91- and 182-day bills and
seven-year bonds.  The yield on the 3.835 percent bond due August 2015 was
3.26 percent. The ringgit was at 3.0975.  To contact the reporters on this story:
